What you need to know:

Watermelon farming is a good agri-enterprise and with good management practices, one can get high yields of up to25-30 tonnes per hectare.Ginger requires heavy rainfall followed by a dry spell. It will do well in areas with an annual rainfall of 1,000-2,000mm.The optimum temperature for ginger production is 25°-30°C. Ginger is mainly grown in the coastal lowlands of Kwale, in Eastern, Mt Elgon, Western and areas around Lake Victoria, but can do well in most parts of the country.